Sevilla sporting director Monchi says his club has not received any offers for reported Manchester United target Wissam Ben Yedder.<br />
<br />
Asked about Ben Yedder, Monchi told Cadena Ser radio: &quot;There's nothing new. He has one week left of holiday and will report for pre-season on the (July) 13th to travel to the United States. From then on, the (transfer) market is open and there are possibilities for any player of our squad. As of today, no offer has arrived.&quot;
